                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-defend1872" type="age" value="30"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             were indicted for <rs id="t18310407-270-off1439" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-off1439" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-off1439" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18310407-270-cd1440" type="crimeDate">27th of March</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-270-off1439 t18310407-270-cd1440"></join>, 1 grafting-tool, value 4s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18310407-270-victim1873" type="victimName">
                  James 
                  Layton
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-victim1873" type="surname" value="Layton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-victim1873" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-victim1873" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-270-off1439 t18310407-270-victim1873"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1874">
                  PETER 
                  DANIELS
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1874" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1874" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1874" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I and the prisoners are <rs id="t18310407-270-deflabel1441" type="occupation">navigators</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-270-defend1870 t18310407-270-deflabel1441"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-270-defend1872 t18310407-270-deflabel1441"></join> - they worked in the same field as me, but not at the same spot. Layton left this tool with me about seven o'clock on Saturday evening, and I put it under the stairs at the <placeName id="t18310407-270-crimeloc1442">Falcon public-house, Stoke Newington</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-270-crimeloc1442" type="placeName" value="Falcon public-house, Stoke Newington"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310407-270-crimeloc1442" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310407-270-off1439 t18310407-270-crimeloc1442"></join>, where I sleep - I missed it about half-past six on Sunday evening - the prisoners were drinking in the tap-room; I went to them and said, "It is very strange you should go into the place and take the tool; it must be somebody who is in the house;" Hadiston followed me outside the door and said, "If you say we stole the tool I will smash you," (holding up his clenched fist) - I said I did not say it was them, but it must be somebody in the house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1875">
                  DANIEL 
                  DAWSON
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1875" type="surname" value="DAWSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1875" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1875" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a retail beer-shop in Stoke Newington. The two prisoner came into the passage leading to my tap-room, in company - I asked what they wanted, they said the boy I employed to take out the beer- I said he was gone out, and asked what they wanted of him - one of them (I don't know which) said, to leave this tool till Monday morning - I said I would take care of it, as they used my house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1876">
                  JOSEPH 
                  MARSHALL
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1876" type="surname" value="MARSHALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1876" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1876" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-constable. I apprehended the prisoners on the 28th of March; they said nothing to me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1877">
                  EDWARD 
                  FREEMAN
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1877" type="surname" value="FREEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1877" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1877" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I got the tool from the beer-shop- I have had it ever since.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1878">
                  JAMES 
                  LAYTON
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1878" type="surname" value="LAYTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1878" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1878" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This is my tool; I left it in Daniel's care.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. How do you know it? A. It is marked with a piece of wire at each end - I never asked for 30s. not to prosecute - 
               <persName id="t18310407-270-person1879">
                  Thomas 
                  McBride
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1879" type="surname" value="McBride"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1879" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1879" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came to me and offered me 30s., but I never asked him for it - I do not know whether any body else was present. but nobody can say I asked him for the money.</p>
               <p>Hadiston's Defence. I am innocent.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-270-person1880">
                  THOMAS 
                  McBRIDE
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1880" type="surname" value="McBRIDE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1880" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1880" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I offered to settle this with Layton - he asked me 5l. at first - he told me if I would not give that before he went before the Magistrate, he would prosecute the men - there had been a subscription raised among their friends.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Did Daniels or Layton want to make it up? - A.Daniels wanted 7s. for two days' work, and Layton wanted 30s. - they had been before the Magistrate once - the prisoners knew themselves innocent, and did not wish the money to be given, but our mates subscribed 30s. - we could not afford to raise 5l. - he afterwards said he would take 30s., which we put into the hands of Mr. Hudson - he said he would keep away from the Magistrate for 3s. 6d. a day.</p>
               <p>JURY to 
               <persName id="t18310407-270-person1881">
                  PETER 
                  DANIELS
               <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1881" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1881" type="given" value="PETER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-270-person1881" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. Did you find the tool at a different house to where you lost it from? A. Yes, I found it at a beer-shop one hundred and fifty yards off.</p>
